 "\n(a) Calculate and interpret Spearman\[CloseCurlyQuote]s rank correlation \
coefficient with pen and paper and then check your results using Mathematica.\
\n(b) Does Spearman\[CloseCurlyQuote]s R differ depending on whether ranks \
are assigned in a decreasing or increasing order? -> ",
 StyleBox["R does not differ: using a decreasing order for the ranks. The sum \
of d_i^2 =8, as before, and hence, the result for R is the same.",
  FontColor->RGBColor[0., 0., 0.]],
 "\n(c) Suppose the coffee can only be rated as either good (>5) or bad (\
\[LessEqual]5). Do the chances of a good rating differ between the two \
journalists?"
}], "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9471186994262543`*^9, 3.947118733473477*^9}, 
   3.947123368091052*^9, {3.9792922558327847`*^9, 3.9792922615313396`*^9}, {
